<paragraph blockId="5.[718,868,1444,1470]" box="[718,868,1444,1470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<heading box="[718,868,1444,1470]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
(
<figureCitation box="[726,861,1444,1470]" captionStart="Figs 19–24" captionStartId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" captionTargetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[319,1267,424,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 19–24. Lepidostoma ahlae sp. n.: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Figs 19–24</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1270,1512,1821]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
Description: Colour dark brown. Scapes (
<figureCitation box="[790,862,1512,1533]" captionStart="Figs 19–24" captionStartId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" captionTargetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[319,1267,424,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 19–24. Lepidostoma ahlae sp. n.: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) each 
<quantity box="[928,1015,1512,1533]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="4.85">4.85 mm</quantity>
in length, with two small subbasal processes dorsally. Maxillary palps (
<figureCitation box="[752,821,1540,1561]" captionStart="Figs 19–24" captionStartId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" captionTargetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[319,1267,424,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 19–24. Lepidostoma ahlae sp. n.: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) each 
<quantity box="[882,969,1540,1561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.94" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.94">1.94 mm</quantity>
, two-segmented, basal segment much longer, apical one with pointed apex, both segments covered with dense setae. Average length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[490,568,1598,1619]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="7.7">7.7 mm</quantity>
. Wing venation as in 
<figureCitation box="[783,880,1598,1619]" captionStart="Figs 19–24" captionStartId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" captionTargetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[319,1267,424,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 19–24. Lepidostoma ahlae sp. n.: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Figure 24</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1270,1512,1821]" lastBlockId="7.[317,1270,1686,1765]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[531,644,1627,1648]" captionStart="Figs 19–24" captionStartId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" captionTargetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[319,1267,424,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 19–24. Lepidostoma ahlae sp. n.: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Figs 19–22</figureCitation>
): Segment IX apicodorsally produced into somewhat rounded tip. Segment X with dorsolateral plates broad at base, apically rounded; mesal processes narrow, situated closely to one another with small space between them; in lateral view dorsolateral plates triangular, apically rounded, with slightly serrate ventral margins, mesal processes somewhat dome-shaped, with very broad bases. Inferior appendages each two-segmented, 1st segment broad at base and narrower towards its apex, 2nd segment short with truncate apex; basodorsal processes absent. Phallus with phallobase and phallicata slender, cylindrical in lateral view. Parameres about as long as phallus scape and palps, right lateral view; 18 = right forewing, dorsal view right lateral view; 24 = right forewing, dorsal view
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732059" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5732059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732059/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" startId="6.[317,360,1759,1780]" targetBox="[318,1269,437,1715]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1759,1838]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[317,433,1759,1780]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Figs 13–18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Parey &amp; Saini, 2012" authorityName="Parey &amp; Saini" authorityYear="2012" box="[440,679,1760,1781]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sonmargae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[440,679,1760,1781]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Lepidostoma sonmargae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[686,741,1759,1780]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 13 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 14 = male genitalia ventral view; 15 = male genitalia, left lateral view; 16 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 17 = head,
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" startId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" targetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[317,1270,1686,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[317,431,1686,1707]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Figs 19–24.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Parey &amp; Saini, 2012" authorityName="Parey &amp; Saini" authorityYear="2012" box="[437,620,1686,1707]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ahlae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[437,620,1686,1707]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Lepidostoma ahlae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[626,679,1686,1707]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps,
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[317,1270,436,486]" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">
and with two paramere spines closely adjacent to one another. Wing venation of this species (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1263,436,457]" captionStart="Figs 19–24" captionStartId="7.[317,360,1686,1707]" captionTargetBox="[319,1267,427,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[319,1267,424,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 19–24. Lepidostoma ahlae sp. n.: 19 = male genitalia, dorsal view; 20 = male genitalia, ventral view; 21 = male left lateral view; 22 = phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 23 = head, scape and palps," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732061/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) similar to that of 
<emphasis box="[488,582,465,486]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">L. inerme</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[317,1270,526,798]" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">
Diagnosis: The male of this species resembles that of 
<emphasis box="[1028,1269,526,552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName box="[1028,1180,526,552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="8" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Lepidostoma</taxonomicName>
inerme
</emphasis>
MCLACHLAN but differs from it by having the dorsolateral processes of segment X in dorsal view rounded, not finger-like, and the mesal processes apically fingerlike, not truncate; when seen laterally, each mesal process appears dome-shaped, not pointed, and each lateral process is rounded, not lobed. Scapes of this species each have two small subbasal processes but those of 
<emphasis box="[920,1030,702,728]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">L. inerme</emphasis>
are without any processes. Maxillary palps of this species have the 2nd segment apically tapering, not apically rounded.
</paragraph>
